{
  "stem": "5357.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then came two twin sisters, before me, Sarah and Rivka.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But unfortunately, when she was a year old, Rivka died of pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then I was born, shortly afterwards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I was, actually, the tenth.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was the youngest, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was a resort area.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- our backyard was facing the forest.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The air was excellent.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People used to come to Otwock summer and winter, because summer we had a river from one side, and the trees that gave off-- what do you call those trees with the long, thin-- that give off-- oren, in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In English, I can't think of the name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have a tree like that in the front-- similar.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Christmas trees are made out of that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pine trees.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The pine trees were very healthy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They soak up the moisture.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And our city was known-- people that were coughing or were sick with TB, they used to come.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in the winter, we had, on the other side, the hills.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They called it the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And people were coming to ski and to go down with those sleds.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I used to go there often, too, in the winter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not on Saturday.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we were Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father allowed us to play with non-Jewish friends, because he knew that whatever we learn at home, that's what's going to stay with us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's how it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And thanks to this, that my father was so, in a way, liberal, we girls could survive among the Polish people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we spoke Polish very well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The boys went to cheder, to a special school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the girls-- my father didn't like the Jewish private schools, because they didn't teach Polish enough.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we took-- he took a Hebrew teacher and he came home to the girls.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
